crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_msg: SERVER-APACHE Oracle WebLogic Apache Connector buffer overflow attempt
crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_raw: alert tcp $EXTERNAL_NET any -> $HOME_NET $HTTP_PORTS ( msg:"SERVER-APACHE Oracle WebLogic Apache Connector buffer overflow attempt"; flow:to_server,established; http_method; content:"POST"; pkt_data; content:"AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA",depth 100; metadata:policy max-detect-ips drop,policy security-ips drop; service:http; reference:bugtraq,30273; reference:cve,2008-3257; reference:url,www.oracle.com/technology/deploy/security/alerts/alert_cve2008-3257.html; classtype:attempted-admin; sid:15511; rev:10; )

crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_msg: POLICY-OTHER HTTP request by IPv4 address attempt
crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_raw: alert tcp any any -> any $HTTP_PORTS ( msg:"POLICY-OTHER HTTP request by IPv4 address attempt"; flow:to_server,established; http_header; content:"Host:",fast_pattern,nocase; pcre:"/^Host\x3a\s*(?:(?:25[0-5]|2[0-4][0-9]|[01]?[0-9]?[0-9])\.){3}(?:25[0-5]|2[0-4][0-9]|[01]?[0-9]?[0-9])\s*:?\s*\d*\s*$/ims"; service:http; reference:url,www.w3.org/Protocols/rfc2616/rfc2616-sec15.html; classtype:policy-violation; sid:50447; rev:1; )
